<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-05-24T07:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-05-24T07:44:00-05:00" n="698" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d698">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">711.8212a/3: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Walton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-05-24T12:00:00-00:44">May 24,
                                    1939—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>35. Reference Department’s instruction No. 124 of March 7th subject
                                conciliation convention. Liberian Government desires to know if
                                expense of the Permanent Commission shall be a continuous charge on
                                the contracting parties or whether those expenses arise only as and
                                when the Commission is called upon to function.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Walton</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>